While encryption focuses on secrecy (privacy),
 Message Authentication Codes focus on
\series bold
 
\series default
\emph on
integrity
\emph default
 (ensuring the message wasn't changed) and 
\emph on
authenticity
\emph default
 (ensuring it really came from Alice).
 These goals are 
\emph on
orthogonal
\emph default
;
 secrecy alone does not guarantee integrity.
